# SENTIMENT CLASSIFICATION 
## Background
Here we get some short sentence which may represent some human feeling, such as anger, fear, joy, love, sadness, or surprise. 
This project focus on how to well handle the text data as well as establish a multi-classifier to figure out the emotion within these sentence.

## Project Structure
doc/
- The final report

data/
- The raw data

evaluation/
- the intermediate score while training and evaluation

model/
- some trained models file such as w2v and lstm

    - utils.py
        - some common function
    - data.py 
        - to construct the dataset class for dataloader
    - model.py
        - define the whole structure of the NN model
    - train.py
        - instruct the training process
        - include every epoch evaluation
    - preprocess.py
        - define a class to handle the input data
    - test.py
        - how the model do a test classification
    - w2v.py
        - train a w2v model and save
    - main.py
        - main process, control even all steps
    - prediction.py
        - to predict the unlabeled data, and get the output file
